compile, we need to restrict the generic type we're\naccepting:\n\n```\nuse std::fmt;\n\n// Restrict the input type to types that implement Debug.\nfn some_func<T: fmt::Debug>(foo: T) {\n    println!(\"{:?}\", foo);\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    // Calling the method is still fine, as i32 implements Debug.\n    some_func(5i32);\n\n    // This would fail to compile now:\n    // struct WithoutDebug;\n    // some_func(WithoutDebug);\n}\n```\n\nRust only looks at the signature of the called function, as such it must\nalready specify all requirements that will be used for every type parameter.\n"},"level":"error","message":"`P` doesn't implement `std::fmt::Debug`","spans":[{"byte_end":95821,"byte_start":95816,"column_end":80,"column_start":75,"expansion":{"def_site_span":{"byte_end":94614,"byte_start":94593,"column_end":22,"column_start":1,"expansion":null,"file_name":"/home/ghuntley/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/tracing-0.1.41/src/macros.rs","is_primary":false,"label":null,"line_end":2784,"line_start":2784,"suggested_replacement":null,"suggestion_applicability":null,"text":[{"highlight_end":22,"highlight_start":1,"text":"macro_rules! valueset {"}]},"macro_decl_name":"$crate::valueset!","span":{"byte_end":101893,"byte_start":101700,"column_end":14,"column_start":31,"expansion":{"def_site_span":{"byte_end":94614,"byte_start":94593,"column_end":22,"column_start":1,"expansion":null,"file_name":"/home/ghuntley/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/tracing-0.1.41/src/macros.rs","is_primary":false,"label":null,"line_end":2784,"line_start":2784,"suggested_replacement":null,"suggestion_applicability":null,"text":[{"highlight_end":22,"highlight_start":1,"text":"macro_rules! valueset {"}]},"macro_decl_name":"$crate::valueset!","span":{"byte_end":2886,"byte_start":2841,"column_end":67,"column_start":22,"expansion":{"def_site_span":{"byte_end":435,"byte_start":418,"column_end":18,"column_start":1,"expansion":null,"file_name":"/home/ghuntley/.cargo/regi